        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="TdW9oKKxsJU2AUWhq7uW-95" parent="1" style="shape=umlFrame;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;pointerEvents=0;width=70;height=40;" value="Fetch List of Places" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="55" width="155" x="580" y="480" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="UWNoiYovL3Yv8UeEzB46-1" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeColor=light-dark(#000000,#F1FF0F);fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#F1FF0B);fontColor=light-dark(#000000,#000000);" value="User will commence in creating an account through which API will validate the information, checking for errors and if successful will process the information through the methods, saving the users information to the Database.&lt;br&gt;Returns confirmed information was saved. if saved,&lt;div&gt;Backend returns response to API.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;API returns the success or failure to user if their account has been created&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="197.5" width="190" x="397.5" y="-715" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="hdZgwrDiKc9ZDYHE6M_5-1" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFF88,#FFFF63);strokeColor=#36393d;fontColor=light-dark(#000000,#000000);fontSize=30;" value="&lt;div&gt;Explanatory Notes:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;A brief description of each API call, outlining the key steps involved and the purpose of the sequence diagram.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Explanation of the flow of interactions, highlighting how each layer contributes to fulfilling the API request.&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="520" width="650" x="1440" y="-950" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="hdZgwrDiKc9ZDYHE6M_5-4" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFF88,#FFFF63);strokeColor=#36393d;fontColor=light-dark(#000000,#000000);" value="&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(0, 0, 0));&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;The purpose of this diagram is to describe the process of fetching a list of places based on user criteria (might be location, cost, availability (STC)).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;A user will initiate a search of places in the website. This request will be passed on&amp;nbsp; by the API to the backend where the request is first validated (spelling check, user status(if customer?), specifications).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;After validation, the backend processes the request which is then passed on to the database where a search is initiated and the resulting list is returned to the backend. The backend will inform the API of the success/failure of the search which upon success the list is passed to the user.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="330" width="220" x="250" y="430" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="hdZgwrDiKc9ZDYHE6M_5-5" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFF88,#FFFF63);strokeColor=#36393d;fontColor=light-dark(#000000,#000000);" value="&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;The purpose of this diagram is to describe the review submission process.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;Customers can only reviews places when they have used them. So, before the customer is allowed to save their review, a validation will check if they have used the place whose result will be passed on by the API to the backend. The backend receives the result and if true will process the request which will save the data to the database. The database will confirm the save and returns that result to the user. This review will be displayed on the place page." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="330" width="220" x="1370" y="15" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
